==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delamination
<hw>De*lam`i*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Formation and separation of lamin⟦ae⟧ or layers; one of the methods
by which the various blastodermic layers of the ovum are
differentiated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This process consists of a concentric splitting of the
cells of the blastosphere into an outer layer (epiblast) and an inner
layer (hypoblast). By the perforation of the resultant two-walled
vesicle, a gastrula results similar to that formed by the process of
invagination.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delapsation</ent>⟦br⟧
